pan of the universe\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20151016211032/http://tycho.usno.navy.mil/systime.html Different systems of measuring time]\n* {{In Our Time|Time|p005465z|Time}}\n* [http://www.iep.utm.edu/time/ Time] in the ''[[Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]'', by Bradley Dowden.\n* {{cite encyclopedia |url=http://plato.stanford.edu/archives/win2004/entries/time-experience |title=The Experience and Perception of Time |last=Le Poidevin |first=Robin |date=Winter 2004 |encyclopedia=The Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy |editor=Edward N. Zalta |accessdate=9 April 2011}}\n* [http://www.dmoz.org/Reference/Time/ Time at Open Directory]\n\n{{Nature nav}}\n{{Time topics}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Time articles: Detailed navigation\n|titlestyle=background:#ee9; border:1px solid silver; padding:0.2em 1em 0.2em 6.5em;\n|list1=\n{{Time measurement and standards}}\n{{Chronology}}\n{{Time in religion and mythology}}\n{{Time in philosophy}}\n{{metaphysics}}\n}}\n{{SI base quantities}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Time| ]]\n[[Category:Concepts in metaphysics]]\n[[Category:Concepts in physics]]\n[[Category:Concepts in the philosophy of mind]]\n[[Category:Concepts in the philosophy of science]]\n[[Category:History of ideas]]\n[[Category:History of philosophy]]\n[[Category:History of science]]\n[[Category:Metaphysical theories]]\n[[Category:Metaphysics]]\n[[Category:Ontology]]\n[[Category:Perception]]\n[[Category:Philosophy of time]]\n[[Category:Physical quantities]]\n[[Category:Qualia]]\n[[Category:Reality]]\n[[Category:SI base quantities]]\n[[Category:Spacetime]]\n", "name_user": "DocWatson42", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eTime as \"unreal\":Performed minor cleanup.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time"}
{"title_page": "42 (school)", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name = 42\n\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image = 42 Logo.svg\n| image_size = 150px\n| image_alt = \n| caption = \n| latin_name = \n| motto = Born2Code\n| motto_lang = \n| mottoeng = \n| established = {{Start date|2013}} (Paris)<br />{{Start date|2016}} (Fremont)\n| closed = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n| type = Private<br />Nonprofit<br />Tuition-free\n| parent = \n| affiliation = \n| endowment = \n| budget = \n| rector = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman = \n| chancellor = \n| president = [[Xavier Niel]]\n| vice-president = \n| superintendent = \n| provost = \n| vice_chancellor = \n| principal = \n| dean = \n| director = Sophie Viger\n| head_label = \n| head = \n| academic_staff = \n| administrative_staff = '''Paris, France:'''<br />29<br />'''Fremont, California:'''<br />9\n| students = '''Paris, France:'''<br />2,550<br />'''Fremont, California:'''<br /> 500\n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| other = \n| city = [[Paris]], [[France]]<br />[[Fremont, California]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| state = \n| province = \n| country = \n| campus = \n| former_names = \n| free_label = Tuition\n| free = Free, fully funded by the school\n| athletics = \n| colours = \n| sports = \n| nickname = \n| mascot = \n| affiliations = \n| website = {{URL|42.us.org}} (US campus)<br/>{{URL|42.fr}} (Paris campus)\n| logo = \n| footnotes = \n| colors = \n}}\n\n'''42''' is a private, nonprofit and tuition-free [[computer programming]] school created and funded by French billionaire [[Xavier Niel]] (founder of the telecommunication company [[Iliad (company)|Illiad]]) with several partners including Nicolas Sadirac (previous director-general of the [[\u00c9cole pour l'informatique et les nouvelles technologies|Epitech]] school in France),<ref>{{cite web|language=fr |url=http://www.ecrans.fr/42-v-la-les-geeks,16142.html |author=Camille G\u00e9vaudan |title=\"42\", v\u2019l\u00e0 les geeks ! |website=ecrans |date=2013}}.</ref> Kwame Yamgnane and Florian Bucher (former executives of Epitech).<ref>{{cite web|language=fr |url=https://lemonde.fr/education/article/2013/03/26/42-l-etrange-ecole-d-informatique-de-xavier-niel_3148142_1473685.html |author=Damien Leloup |title=\"42\", l'\u00e9trange \u00e9cole d'informatique de Xavier Niel |website=lemonde |date=2013 }}.</ref> The school was first opened in Paris in 2013.\n\nOut of more than 80,000 candidates in France, 3,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.journaldunet.com/solutions/emploi-rh/reportage-a-l-ecole-42/une-selection-draconienne.shtml|title=70 000 candidats au d\u00e9part, 900 \u00e9tudiants \u00e0 l'arriv\u00e9e|access-date=2016-08-13}}</ref> were selected to complete a four-week intensive computer programming bootcamp called ''piscine'' (swimming-pool). Any person older than 18<ref>{{cite web |title=42 met fin \u00e0 la limite d\u2019\u00e2ge \u00e0 l\u2019entr\u00e9e |url=https://www.42.fr/42-met-fin-a-limite-dage-a-lentree/ |website=42 |accessdate=29 March 2019}}</ref> can register for the ''piscine'' after completing the logical reasoning tests on the website.\n\nThe school does not have any professors, and is open 24/7. The training is inspired by new modern ways to teach which include [[peer-to-peer]] [[pedagogy]] and [[project-based learning]]. The School has been endorsed by many high-profile people in [[Silicon Valley]] including [[Evan Spiegel]] the co-founder and CEO of [[Snapchat]], Keyvon Beykpour the co-founder and CEO of [[Periscope (app)|Periscope]], [[Stewart Butterfield]] the co-founder and CEO of [[Slack (software)|Slack]], [[Brian Chesky]] the co-founder and CEO of [[Airbnb]], [[Tony Fadell]] the founder and CEO of [[Nest Labs]], [[Jack Dorsey]] the co-Founder and CEO of [[Twitter]], [[Paul Graham (computer programmer)|Paul Graham]], [[venture capitalist]] and co-Founder of [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]], [[Bill Gurley]] [[venture capitalist]] and general partner at [[Benchmark (venture capital firm)|Benchmark]].\n\nThe school is a non-profit organization and is entirely free, being funded by billionaire [[Xavier Niel]] with hundreds of millions of dollars. All the intellectual property belongs to the students.\n42 Silicon Valley is the American campus of 42 chartered as a [[public-benefit nonprofit corporation]] in the [[State of California]] and has been created and funded by the same team from France, in addition to a new partner, the chief operating officer of the American school and former 42 Paris student Brittany Bir.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.42.us.org/the-university/team/|title=Team 42 USA|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> 42 Silicon Valley opened in summer 2016 in [[Fremont, California]] in the [[San Francisco Bay Area]].\n\n42's name is a reference to the [[science fiction]] book ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]'' written by British author [[Douglas Adams]]: in the book 42 is the [[Answer to the Ultimate Question of Life, the Universe, and Everything]].\n\nIn addition to the two official campuses in Paris, France and Fremont, California, the school model was adopted in [[Lyon]], [[Reims]], and [[Mulhouse]], France, as well as in [[Romania]], [[South Africa]], [[Ukraine]], [[Bulgaria]], [[Moldova]],<ref>[https://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/technology/french-educational-model-to-gamify-it-education-in-ukraine-414132.html French educational model to gamify IT education in Ukraine], ''[[Kyiv Post]]'', May 19, 2016</ref> [[Belgium]], [[Russia]], [[Morocco]], the [[Netherlands]], [[Indonesia]], and [[Finland]]<ref>[https://www.lemonde.fr/afrique/article/2018/09/05/1337-l-ecole-marocaine-qui-veut-former-des-genies-du-numerique_5350765_3212.html 1337, l'\u00c9cole qui veut former des g\u00e9nies du num\u00e9rique], ''[[Le Monde]]'', September 05, 2018</ref> with the help and support of 42.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Xavier Niel004.jpg|thumb|200px|French entrepreneur and businessman [[Xavier Niel]] who created and funded 42]]\n\nAnnounced on March 26, 2013, 42 opened its doors on July 15, 2013 for the selection phase called ''La Piscine'' (the swimming-pool).\n\nStudents who passed the first 'Piscines' started training in November 2013.\n\nIn an Editorial,<ref name=\"L'\u00e9dito de Xavier Niel | 42 / born2code\">{{cite web |language=fr |url=http://www.42.fr/ledito-de-xavier-niel/ |title=L'\u00e9dito de Xavier Niel |website=42 |date=2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703051034/http://www.42.fr/ledito-de-xavier-niel/ |archivedate=2014-07-03 }}</ref> Xavier Niel introduced 42, linking the need for it to the state of the French Education.\n\n<blockquote>\"Today, the French system doesn't work. It is stuck between on one side the University, which provides training that is not fitting with what the business world needs but is free and accessible to the largest number. And on the other side the private universities (\u00e9coles priv\u00e9es), expensive, where the formation is fairly qualitative but leaves the greatest number of talents on the side of the road, even geniuses, that we could find in France.\"</blockquote>On May 17, 2016 42 announced they will open a second campus in Fremont, California.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.42.us.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/CP_42_US_17_05_2016.pdf|title=Press release|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> The first selection phase (The \"Piscine\") will start on July 11, 2016.\n\nStudents who passed the first 'Piscines' started training in November 2016.\n\n== Campus and Cost ==\n\n=== Paris Campus, France ===\n\n42 France is located at 96 Boulevard Bessi\u00e8res, in the 17th arrondissement of Paris.<ref>{{cite web|language=fr |url=http://www.universfreebox.com/article/20315/Decouvrez-les-locaux-ultra-design-de-l-ecole-42-de-Xavier-Niel |author=Olivier Viaggi |title=Les locaux ultra design de l'\u00e9cole 42 de Xavier Niel |website=universfreebox |date=2013}}</ref> The building was acquired from the State in 2011 for 12.6 million euros. The building extends over an area of 4242 square meters. Pictures of the school architecture are visible on the official website. 42 was designed by IN&EDIT Architecture agency.<ref>{{cite web |language=fr |url=http://www.ineditarchitecture.com |title=\u00c9cole 42}}</ref>\n\n=== Fremont Campus, USA ===\n[[File:42 Silicon Valley Logo.svg|250px|thumb|Logo of 42 Silicon Valley, the American campus of the school]]\n\nThe 42 Silicon Valley building is located at 6600 Dumbarton Circle, in Fremont, California.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.42.us.org/media/|title=Adress 42|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> The building was acquired from DeVry University. The campus is approximately 200,000 sq ft.\n\nThis campus has 300 spaces in the dormitories (titled \"Nostromo Dorms,\" located at 34793 Ardentech Court, Fremont, CA 94555) which are completely free of cost.<ref name=\":0\" /> Like the Paris campus, 42 Silicon Valley was designed by AR architectures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ar.fr/projects/42-us|title=AR website|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Cost ===\n\nThere are no tuition fees for the entirety of the program. All the running costs for the 10 first years have been personally funded by [[Xavier Niel]] a French entrepreneur and philanthropist who founded the French company [[Iliad SA|Iliad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lemondeinformatique.fr/actualites/lire-free-ouvre-l-ecole-42-pour-former-au-numerique-52988.html|title=Free ouvre l'\u00e9cole 42 pour former au num\u00e9rique|date=2013|website=lemondeinformatique|language=fr|author=Jacques Cheminat et Serge Leblal}}.</ref> The 42 Silicon Valley campus also has free dorms for those who are the most in need.\n\n== Application and Admission  ==\nThe candidates must be 18 years or older.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.42.us.org/42-admissions-overview-requirements-process/admissions-requirements/ |title=42 Silicon Valley Admissions |website=Ecole 42 USA}}</ref> No previous diploma is required.\n\nThe selection process begins by taking a few online memory and logic tests, which are intended to evaluate an individual's capacity to learn computer programming.\n\nAfter this there is a second selection which is called the \"Piscine\" which is an intensive programming session in [[C (programming language)|C programming language]] which takes place over a period of 4 weeks.\n\n== Tuition Style ==\n42 does not have lectures or practical work supervised by teachers. Students carry out projects proposed by the pedagogic team, and are free to organise their own time.\n\nThe schools are open 24/7. Students help each other and use the Internet for their projects.\n\nStudents have no time limits in which to complete their projects.  They validate the projects by correcting each other's work. Validation of a project increases the level of the students, allowing them to unlock new and more difficult challenges.\n\nDuring their time at the school, students have to undertake internships. To qualify for an internship a student must have validated a certain number of projects and passed five exams.\n\nMany entrepreneurs hold conferences at the school.  42 school has also forged partnerships with other schools (business schools, design schools etc.) and the [[hackathon]] organisation. Students are able to participate in partnership activities if they wish to.\n\n== Academics ==\n\nAfter the \"''Piscine\"'', training lasts at least three years, and covers the different I.T. jobs linked to development.\n\nThe beginning of the program is mainly focused on the [[Unix]] development environment with the [[C (programming language)|C-language]]. These software developments are planned through 40 projects such as the implementation of a basic [[First-person shooter]] engine, an engine for an online game and a 3D rendering engine ([[rasterizer]]) by ray tracing.\n\nAfter that there are a lot of other languages students will see like [[PHP]], [[C++]], [[OCaml|OCAML]] and many others. Some projects can also have free language choice.\n\nAccording to a promotional document about the school program, learning software development is planned through the realization of an arcade game, artificial intelligence or a computer virus.\n\n42 students and people from everywhere in the world can create a new project if they want.\n\n== Endorsement ==\n[[File:Bolden42.jpg|thumb|400x400px|[[Charles Bolden|Charles F. Bolden]] from [[NASA]] at 42]]\n\nEndorsement in the video for the introduction of the 42 Silicon Valley campus in Fremont, California:\n\n* [[Evan Spiegel]] - Co-founder and CEO at [[Snapchat]]\n* [[Leila Janah]] - Co-founder and CEO at Sama\n* Keyvon Beykpour - Co-founder and CEO at [[Periscope (app)|Periscope]]\n* [[Matt Cohler]] & [[Peter Fenton (venture capitalist)|Peter Fenton]] - General partner at Benchmark\n* David Marcus - VP of messaging products at [[Facebook]]\n* [[Blake Masters (author)|Blake Masters]] - President of the [[Thiel Foundation]]\n* Alexa Scordato - Director of product marketing at [[Stack Overflow]]\n* [[Stewart Butterfield]] - Co-founder and CEO at [[Slack (software)|Slack]]\n* [[Lo\u00efc Le Meur|Loic le Meur]] - Creator of Leade.rs\n* [[Karlie Kloss]] - Founder of Kode with Klossy\n* [[Tony Fadell]] - Founder of [[Nest Labs|Nest]]\n* [[Paul Graham (computer programmer)|Paul Graham]] - Founder of [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]]\n\nPersonalities who came at a 42 Campus for a conference or a visit:\n\n* The French President [[Emmanuel Macron]]\n* American ambassadors to France [[Charles Rivkin]] and [[Jamie McCourt]]\n* The former French President [[Fran\u00e7ois Hollande]]\n* Ministers from French Government : [[Myriam El Khomri|Myriam El-Khomri]], [[Najat Vallaud-Belkacem]], [[Laurent Fabius]], [[Alain Jupp\u00e9]], [[Thierry Mandon]] and [[Patrick Kanner]] \n* The mayor of [[Paris]] [[Anne Hidalgo]] \n* Minister from [[Luxembourg]] Government : [[Nicolas Schmit]]\n* [[Tony Fadell]] - Founder of [[Nest Labs|Nest]]\n* [[Charles Bolden|Charles F. Bolden]] - [[NASA]] administrator\n* [[Richard Stallman]] - Creator of the [[free software movement]]\n* [[Chris Cox (Facebook)|Chris Cox]] - CPO at Facebook\n\n==  Other schools (licensed - same program) ==\n\nOther schools stress educational methodologies such as [[Peer learning|peer-learning]], whereby students are encouraged to assist one-another and self-organize, and [[project-based learning]] which favors longer-term, open-ended assignments.\n\n'''Codecool'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.codecool.com/ |title=Codecool |website=Codecool}}</ref> (Hungary - created in 2014): Codecool is a Budapest based IT EduTech startup which offers a new approach to teaching computer programming with the help of mentors, who guide and transfer knowledge without giving the solution. Working on weekly real life projects with their peers, students graduate with experience required by the market. The 12-month coding course comes with a job placement guarantee that has a 98% success rate.\u00a0\n\n'''WeThinkCode'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wethinkcode.co.za/ |title=WeThinkCode |website=We Think Code}}</ref> (South Africa - created in 2016): WeThinkCode is a new kind of tech incubator dedicated to eliminate the IT skills gap. WeThinkCode's mission is to source and train Africa's future coding talent. Based on the 42 school programs.\n\n'''ACADEMY+PLUS'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.academyplus.ro/ |title=ACADEMY+PLUS |website=Academy Plus |access-date=2016-06-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009013121/https://www.academyplus.ro/ |archive-date=2018-10-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> (Romania - created in 2014): ACADEMY + PLUS has a completely innovative approach on education: working on projects, peer-learning, the results are measurable, it practically encourages teamwork.\na two-year program. The curriculum structure and payment model largely resemble Make university's. Based on the 42 school programs.\n\n'''ACADEMY+MOLDOVA'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.academyplus.md/ |title=ACADEMY+PLUS Moldova |website=Academy Plus Moldova |access-date=2016-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715051631/http://academyplus.md/ |archive-date=2016-07-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref> (Moldova - created in 2016): Academy+Moldova is an alternative and free IT school, launched by Foundation IT Moldova in partnership with the Academy+Plus Cluj-Napoca and Ecole 42 Paris.\n\n'''[[:uk:UNIT Factory|UNIT Factory]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://unit.ua//|title=UNIT Factory|last=|first=|date=|website=UNIT Factory|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> (Kyiv, Ukraine - created in 2016): UNIT Factory is an innovative institution which was created as a joint project of Vasily Khmelnytsky's fund entitled as \"K.Fund\" and 42 (school) which is supported by public institution \"Osvitoriya\".\n\n'''[https://www.le-101.fr Le 101]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.le-101.fr/ |title=The101 |website=The 101}}</ref> (Lyon, France - created in 2017)\n\n'''[https://s19.be 19]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.s19.be/ |title=19 |website=19}}</ref> (Brussels, Belgium - created in 2018)\n\n'''[https://www.codam.nl CODAM]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.codam.nl/ |title=Codam |website=CODAM}}</ref> (Amsterdam, The Netherlands - created in 2018): CODAM is the initiative of [[Corinne Vigreux]], an entrepreneur who co\u2013founded [[TomTom]] and has always been passionate about technology, innovation and social mobility. Codam builds on the pioneering work of Ecole 42 in Paris.\n\n'''[https://1337.ma 1337]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://1337.ma/ |title=1337 |website=1337}}</ref> (Khouribga, Morocco - created in 2018 & Ben guerir, Morocco - created in 2019<ref>{{cite web | url=https://twitter.com/1337FIL/status/1103273477337960448 | title=New Campus | date=6 March 2019 | website=twitter.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://1337.ma/Benguerir | title=CAMPUS BEN GUERIR | date=6 March 2019 | website=1337.ma}}</ref>): 1337 was created as part of an educational partnership between [[OCP Group]] and Paris 42.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leseco.ma/enseignement/535-enseignement/69607-la-premiere-ecole-1337-ouvre-ses-portes-a-khouribga-video.html |title=1337, dans les algorithmes d'une \u00e9cole pas comme les autres |website=leseco.ma}}</ref>\n\n'''[https://21-school.ru 21]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://21-school.ru/ |title=21 |website=\u0428\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430 21 (School 21)}}</ref> (Moscow, Russia - created in 2018): School 21 is launched by [[Sberbank of Russia]] and currently accepting applications. Education is free and lasts from 1.5 to 4 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sberbank.ru/en/press_center/all/article?newsID=58cc01b5-2282-4aca-9b17-5f7981f00281 |title=7,000 applications submitted to Sberbank\u2019s School 21 in first week |website=Sberbank}}</ref>\n\n'''[https://www.hive.fi/en/ Hive]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hive.fi/en/ |title=Hive |website=Hive}}</ref> (Helsinki, Finland - created in 2019)\n\n[https://www.42madrid.com/ 42 Madrid] (Madrid, Spain - created in 2019)\n\n[https://www.42sp.org.br/ 42 Sao Paulo] (Sao Paulo, Brazil - created in 2019)\n\n[https://www.42.rio/ 42 RIO] (Rio de Janeiro, Brazil - created in 2019)\n\n[https://42seoul.kr/ 42 Seoul] (Seoul, South Korea - created in 2019)\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://42.us.org}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n<!-- Categories -->\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in France]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Education in Paris]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:Education in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Coding schools]]\n[[Category:International schools]]\n[[Category:International college and university associations and consortia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name = 42\n\n| native_name = \n| native_name_lang = \n| image = 42 Logo.svg\n| image_size = 150px\n| image_alt = \n| caption = \n| latin_name = \n| motto = Born2Code\n| motto_lang = \n| mottoeng = \n| established = {{Start date|2013}} (Paris)<br />{{Start date|2016}} (Fremont)\n| closed = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n| type = Private<br />Nonprofit<br />Tuition-free\n| parent = \n| affiliation = \n| endowment = \n| budget = \n| rector = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman = \n| chancellor = \n| president = [[Xavier Niel]]\n| vice-president = \n| superintendent = \n| provost = \n| vice_chancellor = \n| principal = \n| dean = \n| director = Sophie Viger\n| head_label = \n| head = \n| academic_staff = \n| administrative_staff = '''Paris, France:'''<br />29<br />'''Fremont, California:'''<br />9\n| students = '''Paris, France:'''<br />2,550<br />'''Fremont, California:'''<br /> 500\n| undergrad = \n| postgrad = \n| doctoral = \n| other = \n| city = [[Paris]], [[France]]<br />[[Fremont, California]], [[United States|U.S.]]\n| state = \n| province = \n| country = \n| campus = \n| former_names = \n| free_label = Tuition\n| free = Free, fully funded by the school\n| athletics = \n| colours = \n| sports = \n| nickname = \n| mascot = \n| affiliations = \n| website = {{URL|42.us.org}} (US campus)<br/>{{URL|42.fr}} (Paris campus)\n| logo = \n| footnotes = \n| colors = \n}}\n\n'''42''' is a private, nonprofit and tuition-free [[computer programming]] school created and funded by French billionaire [[Xavier Niel]] (founder of the telecommunication company [[Iliad (company)|Illiad]]) with several partners including Nicolas Sadirac (previous director-general of the [[\u00c9cole pour l'informatique et les nouvelles technologies|Epitech]] school in France),<ref>{{cite web|language=fr |url=http://www.ecrans.fr/42-v-la-les-geeks,16142.html |author=Camille G\u00e9vaudan |title=\"42\", v\u2019l\u00e0 les geeks ! |website=ecrans |date=2013}}.</ref> Kwame Yamgnane and Florian Bucher (former executives of Epitech).<ref>{{cite web|language=fr |url=https://lemonde.fr/education/article/2013/03/26/42-l-etrange-ecole-d-informatique-de-xavier-niel_3148142_1473685.html |author=Damien Leloup |title=\"42\", l'\u00e9trange \u00e9cole d'informatique de Xavier Niel |website=lemonde |date=2013 }}.</ref> The school was first opened in Paris in 2013.\n\nOut of more than 80,000 candidates in France, 3,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.journaldunet.com/solutions/emploi-rh/reportage-a-l-ecole-42/une-selection-draconienne.shtml|title=70 000 candidats au d\u00e9part, 900 \u00e9tudiants \u00e0 l'arriv\u00e9e|access-date=2016-08-13}}</ref> were selected to complete a four-week intensive computer programming bootcamp called ''piscine'' (swimming-pool). Any person older than 18<ref>{{cite web |title=42 met fin \u00e0 la limite d\u2019\u00e2ge \u00e0 l\u2019entr\u00e9e |url=https://www.42.fr/42-met-fin-a-limite-dage-a-lentree/ |website=42 |accessdate=29 March 2019}}</ref> can register for the ''piscine'' after completing the logical reasoning tests on the website.\n\nThe school does not have any professors, and is open 24/7. The training is inspired by new modern ways to teach which include [[peer-to-peer]] [[pedagogy]] and [[project-based learning]]. The School has been endorsed by many high-profile people in [[Silicon Valley]] including [[Evan Spiegel]] the co-founder and CEO of [[Snapchat]], Keyvon Beykpour the co-founder and CEO of [[Periscope (app)|Periscope]], [[Stewart Butterfield]] the co-founder and CEO of [[Slack (software)|Slack]], [[Brian Chesky]] the co-founder and CEO of [[Airbnb]], [[Tony Fadell]] the founder and CEO of [[Nest Labs]], [[Jack Dorsey]] the co-Founder and CEO of [[Twitter]], [[Paul Graham (computer programmer)|Paul Graham]], [[venture capitalist]] and co-Founder of [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]], [[Bill Gurley]] [[venture capitalist]] and general partner at [[Benchmark (venture capital firm)|Benchmark]].\n\nThe school is a non-profit organization and is entirely free, being funded by billionaire [[Xavier Niel]] with hundreds of millions of dollars. All the intellectual property belongs to the students.\n42 Silicon Valley is the American campus of 42 chartered as a [[public-benefit nonprofit corporation]] in the [[State of California]] and has been created and funded by the same team from France, in addition to a new partner, the chief operating officer of the American school and former 42 Paris student Brittany Bir.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.42.us.org/the-university/team/|title=Team 42 USA|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> 42 Silicon Valley opened in summer 2016 in [[Fremont, California]] in the [[San Francisco Bay Area]].\n\n42's name is a reference to the [[science fiction]] book ''[[The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy]]'' written by British author [[Douglas Adams]]: in the book 42 is the [[Answer to the Ultimate Question of Life, the Universe, and Everything]].\n\nIn addition to the two official campuses in Paris, France and Fremont, California, the school model was adopted in [[Lyon]], [[Reims]], and [[Mulhouse]], France, as well as in [[Romania]], [[South Africa]], [[Ukraine]], [[Bulgaria]], [[Moldova]],<ref>[https://www.kyivpost.com/article/content/technology/french-educational-model-to-gamify-it-education-in-ukraine-414132.html French educational model to gamify IT education in Ukraine], ''[[Kyiv Post]]'', May 19, 2016</ref> [[Belgium]], [[Russia]], [[Morocco]], the [[Netherlands]], [[Indonesia]], and [[Finland]]<ref>[https://www.lemonde.fr/afrique/article/2018/09/05/1337-l-ecole-marocaine-qui-veut-former-des-genies-du-numerique_5350765_3212.html 1337, l'\u00c9cole qui veut former des g\u00e9nies du num\u00e9rique], ''[[Le Monde]]'', September 05, 2018</ref> with the help and support of 42.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Xavier Niel004.jpg|thumb|200px|French entrepreneur and businessman [[Xavier Niel]] who created and funded 42]]\n\nAnnounced on March 26, 2013, 42 opened its doors on July 15, 2013 for the selection phase called ''La Piscine'' (the swimming-pool).\n\nStudents who passed the first 'Piscines' started training in November 2013.\n\nIn an Editorial,<ref name=\"L'\u00e9dito de Xavier Niel | 42 / born2code\">{{cite web |language=fr |url=http://www.42.fr/ledito-de-xavier-niel/ |title=L'\u00e9dito de Xavier Niel |website=42 |date=2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140703051034/http://www.42.fr/ledito-de-xavier-niel/ |archivedate=2014-07-03 }}</ref> Xavier Niel introduced 42, linking the need for it to the state of the French Education.\n\n<blockquote>\"Today, the French system doesn't work. It is stuck between on one side the University, which provides training that is not fitting with what the business world needs but is free and accessible to the largest number. And on the other side the private universities (\u00e9coles priv\u00e9es), expensive, where the formation is fairly qualitative but leaves the greatest number of talents on the side of the road, even geniuses, that we could find in France.\"</blockquote>On May 17, 2016 42 announced they will open a second campus in Fremont, California.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.42.us.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/CP_42_US_17_05_2016.pdf|title=Press release|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> The first selection phase (The \"Piscine\") will start on July 11, 2016.\n\nStudents who passed the first 'Piscines' started training in November 2016.\n\n== Campus and Cost ==\n\n\n=== Paris Campus, France ===\n\n42 France is located at 96 Boulevard Bessi\u00e8res, in the 17th arrondissement of Paris.<ref>{{cite web|language=fr |url=http://www.universfreebox.com/article/20315/Decouvrez-les-locaux-ultra-design-de-l-ecole-42-de-Xavier-Niel |author=Olivier Viaggi |title=Les locaux ultra design de l'\u00e9cole 42 de Xavier Niel |website=universfreebox |date=2013}}</ref> The building was acquired from the State in 2011 for 12.6 million euros. The building extends over an area of 4242 square meters. Pictures of the school architecture are visible on the official website. 42 was designed by IN&EDIT Architecture agency.<ref>{{cite web |language=fr |url=http://www.ineditarchitecture.com |title=\u00c9cole 42}}</ref>\n\n=== Fremont Campus, USA ===\n[[File:42 Silicon Valley Logo.svg|250px|thumb|Logo of 42 Silicon Valley, the American campus of the school]]\n\nThe 42 Silicon Valley building is located at 6600 Dumbarton Circle, in Fremont, California.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.42.us.org/media/|title=Adress 42|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> The building was acquired from DeVry University. The campus is approximately 200,000 sq ft.\n\nThis campus has 300 spaces in the dormitories (titled \"Nostromo Dorms,\" located at 34793 Ardentech Court, Fremont, CA 94555) which are completely free of cost.<ref name=\":0\" /> Like the Paris campus, 42 Silicon Valley was designed by AR architectures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ar.fr/projects/42-us|title=AR website|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n=== Cost ===\n\nThere are no tuition fees for the entirety of the program. All the running costs for the 10 first years have been personally funded by [[Xavier Niel]] a French entrepreneur and philanthropist who founded the French company [[Iliad SA|Iliad]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lemondeinformatique.fr/actualites/lire-free-ouvre-l-ecole-42-pour-former-au-numerique-52988.html|title=Free ouvre l'\u00e9cole 42 pour former au num\u00e9rique|date=2013|website=lemondeinformatique|language=fr|author=Jacques Cheminat et Serge Leblal}}.</ref> The 42 Silicon Valley campus also has free dorms for those who are the most in need.\n\n== Application and Admission  ==\nThe candidates must be 18 years or older.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.42.us.org/42-admissions-overview-requirements-process/admissions-requirements/ |title=42 Silicon Valley Admissions |website=Ecole 42 USA}}</ref> No previous diploma is required.\n\nThe selection process begins by taking a few online memory and logic tests, which are intended to evaluate an individual's capacity to learn computer programming.\n\nAfter this there is a second selection which is called the \"Piscine\" which is an intensive programming session in [[C (programming language)|C programming language]] which takes place over a period of 4 weeks.\n\n== Tuition Style ==\n42 does not have lectures or practical work supervised by teachers. Students carry out projects proposed by the pedagogic team, and are free to organise their own time.\n\nThe schools are open 24/7. Students help each other and use the Internet for their projects.\n\nStudents have no time limits in which to complete their projects.  They validate the projects by correcting each other's work. Validation of a project increases the level of the students, allowing them to unlock new and more difficult challenges.\n\nDuring their time at the school, students have to undertake internships. To qualify for an internship a student must have validated a certain number of projects and passed five exams.\n\nMany entrepreneurs hold conferences at the school.  42 school has also forged partnerships with other schools (business schools, design schools etc.) and the [[hackathon]] organisation. Students are able to participate in partnership activities if they wish to.\n\n== Academics ==\n\nAfter the \"''Piscine\"'', training lasts at least three years, and covers the different I.T. jobs linked to development.\n\nThe beginning of the program is mainly focused on the [[Unix]] development environment with the [[C (programming language)|C-language]]. These software developments are planned through 40 projects such as the implementation of a basic [[First-person shooter]] engine, an engine for an online game and a 3D rendering engine ([[rasterizer]]) by ray tracing.\n\nAfter that there are a lot of other languages students will see like [[PHP]], [[C++]], [[OCaml|OCAML]] and many others. Some projects can also have free language choice.\n\nAccording to a promotional document about the school program, learning software development is planned through the realization of an arcade game, artificial intelligence or a computer virus.\n\n42 students and people from everywhere in the world can create a new project if they want.\n\n== Endorsement ==\n[[File:Bolden42.jpg|thumb|400x400px|[[Charles Bolden|Charles F. Bolden]] from [[NASA]] at 42]]\n\nEndorsement in the video for the introduction of the 42 Silicon Valley campus in Fremont, California:\n\n* [[Evan Spiegel]] - Co-founder and CEO at [[Snapchat]]\n* [[Leila Janah]] - Co-founder and CEO at Sama\n* Keyvon Beykpour - Co-founder and CEO at [[Periscope (app)|Periscope]]\n* [[Matt Cohler]] & [[Peter Fenton (venture capitalist)|Peter Fenton]] - General partner at Benchmark\n* David Marcus - VP of messaging products at [[Facebook]]\n* [[Blake Masters (author)|Blake Masters]] - President of the [[Thiel Foundation]]\n* Alexa Scordato - Director of product marketing at [[Stack Overflow]]\n* [[Stewart Butterfield]] - Co-founder and CEO at [[Slack (software)|Slack]]\n* [[Lo\u00efc Le Meur|Loic le Meur]] - Creator of Leade.rs\n* [[Karlie Kloss]] - Founder of Kode with Klossy\n* [[Tony Fadell]] - Founder of [[Nest Labs|Nest]]\n* [[Paul Graham (computer programmer)|Paul Graham]] - Founder of [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]]\n\nPersonalities who came at a 42 Campus for a conference or a visit:\n\n* The French President [[Emmanuel Macron]]\n* American ambassadors to France [[Charles Rivkin]] and [[Jamie McCourt]]\n* The former French President [[Fran\u00e7ois Hollande]]\n* Ministers from French Government : [[Myriam El Khomri|Myriam El-Khomri]], [[Najat Vallaud-Belkacem]], [[Laurent Fabius]], [[Alain Jupp\u00e9]], [[Thierry Mandon]] and [[Patrick Kanner]] \n* The mayor of [[Paris]] [[Anne Hidalgo]] \n* Minister from [[Luxembourg]] Government : [[Nicolas Schmit]]\n* [[Tony Fadell]] - Founder of [[Nest Labs|Nest]]\n* [[Charles Bolden|Charles F. Bolden]] - [[NASA]] administrator\n* [[Richard Stallman]] - Creator of the [[free software movement]]\n* [[Chris Cox (Facebook)|Chris Cox]] - CPO at Facebook\n\n==  Other schools (licensed - same program) ==\n\nOther schools stress educational methodologies such as [[Peer learning|peer-learning]], whereby students are encouraged to assist one-another and self-organize, and [[project-based learning]] which favors longer-term, open-ended assignments.\n\n'''Codecool'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.codecool.com/ |title=Codecool |website=Codecool}}</ref> (Hungary - created in 2014): Codecool is a Budapest based IT EduTech startup which offers a new approach to teaching computer programming with the help of mentors, who guide and transfer knowledge without giving the solution. Working on weekly real life projects with their peers, students graduate with experience required by the market. The 12-month coding course comes with a job placement guarantee that has a 98% success rate.\u00a0\n\n'''WeThinkCode'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.wethinkcode.co.za/ |title=WeThinkCode |website=We Think Code}}</ref> (South Africa - created in 2016): WeThinkCode is a new kind of tech incubator dedicated to eliminate the IT skills gap. WeThinkCode's mission is to source and train Africa's future coding talent. Based on the 42 school programs.\n\n'''ACADEMY+PLUS'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.academyplus.ro/ |title=ACADEMY+PLUS |website=Academy Plus |access-date=2016-06-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181009013121/https://www.academyplus.ro/ |archive-date=2018-10-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref> (Romania - created in 2014): ACADEMY + PLUS has a completely innovative approach on education: working on projects, peer-learning, the results are measurable, it practically encourages teamwork.\na two-year program. The curriculum structure and payment model largely resemble Make university's. Based on the 42 school programs.\n\n'''ACADEMY+MOLDOVA'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.academyplus.md/ |title=ACADEMY+PLUS Moldova |website=Academy Plus Moldova |access-date=2016-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160715051631/http://academyplus.md/ |archive-date=2016-07-15 |url-status=dead }}</ref> (Moldova - created in 2016): Academy+Moldova is an alternative and free IT school, launched by Foundation IT Moldova in partnership with the Academy+Plus Cluj-Napoca and Ecole 42 Paris.\n\n'''[[:uk:UNIT_Factory|UNIT Factory]]'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://unit.ua//|title=UNIT Factory|last=|first=|date=|website=UNIT Factory|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> (Kyiv, Ukraine - created in 2016): UNIT Factory is an innovative institution which was created as a joint project of Vasily Khmelnytsky's fund entitled as \"K.Fund\" and 42 (school) which is supported by public institution \"Osvitoriya\".\n\n'''[https://www.le-101.fr Le 101]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.le-101.fr/ |title=The101 |website=The 101}}</ref> (Lyon, France - created in 2017)\n\n'''[https://s19.be 19]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.s19.be/ |title=19 |website=19}}</ref> (Brussels, Belgium - created in 2018)\n\n'''[https://www.codam.nl CODAM]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.codam.nl/ |title=Codam |website=CODAM}}</ref> (Amsterdam, The Netherlands - created in 2018): CODAM is the initiative of [[Corinne Vigreux]], an entrepreneur who co\u2013founded [[TomTom]] and has always been passionate about technology, innovation and social mobility. Codam builds on the pioneering work of Ecole 42 in Paris.\n\n'''[https://1337.ma 1337]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://1337.ma/ |title=1337 |website=1337}}</ref> (Khouribga, Morocco - created in 2018 & Ben guerir, Morocco - created in 2019<ref>{{cite web | url=https://twitter.com/1337FIL/status/1103273477337960448 | title=New Campus | date=6 March 2019 | website=twitter.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://1337.ma/Benguerir | title=CAMPUS BEN GUERIR | date=6 March 2019 | website=1337.ma}}</ref>): 1337 was created as part of an educational partnership between [[OCP Group]] and Paris 42.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.leseco.ma/enseignement/535-enseignement/69607-la-premiere-ecole-1337-ouvre-ses-portes-a-khouribga-video.html |title=1337, dans les algorithmes d'une \u00e9cole pas comme les autres |website=leseco.ma}}</ref>\n\n'''[https://21-school.ru 21]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://21-school.ru/ |title=21 |website=\u0428\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430 21 (School 21)}}</ref> (Moscow, Russia - created in 2018): School 21 is launched by [[Sberbank of Russia]] and currently accepting applications. Education is free and lasts from 1.5 to 4 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sberbank.ru/en/press_center/all/article?newsID=58cc01b5-2282-4aca-9b17-5f7981f00281 |title=7,000 applications submitted to Sberbank\u2019s School 21 in first week |website=Sberbank}}</ref>\n\n'''[https://www.hive.fi/en/ Hive]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hive.fi/en/ |title=Hive |website=Hive}}</ref> (Helsinki, Finland - created in 2019)\n\n[https://www.42madrid.com/ 42 Madrid] (Madrid, Spain - created in 2019)\n\n[https://www.42sp.org.br/ 42 Sao Paulo] (Sao Paulo, Brazil - created in 2019)\n\n[https://www.42.rio/ 42 RIO] (Rio de Janeiro, Brazil - created in 2019)\n\n[https://42seoul.kr/ 42 Seoul] (Seoul, South Korea - created in 2019)\n\n== References ==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://42.us.org}}\n\n<!-- Categories -->\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in France]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2013]]\n[[Category:Education in Paris]]\n[[Category:2013 establishments in France]]\n[[Category:Education in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Coding schools]]\n[[Category:International schools]]\n[[Category:International college and university associations and consortia]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//